It looks like the model describes the relationship fairly wellâhowever, I look at the right half of the graph, and I feel like I see the data points above the curve getting further and further from our model line. This gives me pause, and Iâm curious to see the residuals.

ggplot(pred_data,
       aes(x = log_followers,
           y = .resid)) +

There are some large residuals, although generally I think that the model appears to do a very good job in relation to our data. The large residuals happen at very low values of followers, as well as at relatively high values of followers. However, I donât think that there is a pattern in the residuals that would indicate a poor modeling.
